According to CNN, attacks on Kenyan and Nigerian students have been reported in Greater Noida this week. JOHANNESBURG - African citizens living in northern India are locking themselves indoors after a spate of mob attacks.According to CNN, attacks on Kenyan and Nigerian students have been reported in Greater Noida this week.The city is situated almost 30km south-east of the capital New Delhi.Officials have confirmed a woman in her 20s was admitted to hospital on Tuesday.The Association of African Students in India issued a warning on social media.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)